.TH "ubifs_add_bud_to_log" 9 "ubifs_add_bud_to_log" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubifs_add_bud_to_log \- add a new bud to the log.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubifs_add_bud_to_log
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "int jhead "  ","
.BI "int lnum "  ","
.BI "int offs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "jhead" 12
journal head the bud belongs to
.IP "lnum" 12
LEB number of the bud
.IP "offs" 12
starting offset of the bud
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function writes a reference node for the new bud LEB \fIlnum\fP to the log,
and adds it to the buds trees. It also makes sure that log size does not
exceed the 'c->max_bud_bytes' limit. Returns zero in case of success,
-EAGAIN if commit is required, and a negative error code in case of
failure.
